[start section id="$final"]
Final Diagnosis
A.  Colon, sigmoid, rectum, and anus, abdomino-perineal resection:  Biopsy changes present in the distal aspect of the specimen, extending to the dentate line, and including mucosal ulceration, chronic inflammation, crypt distortion and foreign body giant cell reaction.  No residual carcinoma seen (entire area of biopsy site submitted for histologic evaluation).  Multiple (27) lymph nodes are negative for metastatic carcinoma.

With available material: AJCC pT1N0
See case CR10-2984 for depth of invasion of adenocarcinoma


[end section id="$final"]
[start section id="$gross"]

Gross Description
A.  Received fresh labeled ""sigmoid and rectum"" is an abdominal perineal resection specimen consisting of 28.0 cm in length portion of rectum and colon with a 4.5 cm portion of anus.  A 2.0 x 2.0 x 1.3 cm flat lesion is present within the distal rectum at the dentate line, 0.9 cm from the anal mucosal margin, 2.0 cm from the anal skin margin, and 2.6 cm from the radial margin.  Tumor perforation is absent.  Multiple lymph nodes are identified within the perirectal fat.  Representative sections are submitted.  Grossed by LOPEZ.



Frozen Sect-Intraop
A.  Colon, resection:  Biopsy changes present; without residual carcinoma.  Hold over for submission of entire area.

Frozen section histologic interpretation performed by:  Jamie L. Darrow, M.D.





[end section id="$gross"]